node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Ian Prukner in Siesta Key, Florida. May be an image of 4 people, people standing and text.

node.text:
3 leadership lessons I learned from Flavor Flav 🔥🔥

So the Girls and I got to spend a few minutes tonight with this music Icon🙌🏻

and honestly , i was inspired and convicted to do better 

i meet so many people all the time, and so many people want my time and attention that sometimes it’s a little overwhelming .. but He reminded me of this: it’s ALWAYS about the people not about us 

He spent several minutes talking to the girls about their school and the sports they were involved in
He even encouraged Zoey about her upcoming soccer tryouts !

so Here’s 3 leadership lessons i learned from him 

1. No matter how important you are, you can always find a way to make people feel special - he made my girls feel like they were the superstars 

2. Take an interest in others- spend a minute , slow down and take an interest in people. - He could have reluctantly taken a picture and went about his business but he stood and talked with the girls about their lives…they couldn’t believe it 

3. Always have a kind word- you never know what people are going through and sometimes an encouraging word at the right time can make all the difference - when He told Zoey that he knew she would do great at her soccer tryout it made her night 

i think no matter who we are we can all learn from flavor flav here and be better to the people in our lives! 

drop a 🔥🔥 if this spoke to you

node.text:
some people leave millions of 💰💰 when they leave this earth and some leave millions of excuses 

now i’m a big believer that it’s not just what you leave to people that’s important … but it’s also what you leave “in” people

but here’s the facts : you can take the NO’S or you can pass them down to your family to take 

if you don’t handle them your kids are going to have to 

what’s my point? 

i always wanted to be the one that would change things for my family 

the one who would give my today’s for their tomorrows

the one who would pay the price now so
i could pay any price later 

in life someone is going to have to do the hard things, take the no’s , do it day in and day out despite how they feel … for years 

someone is going to have to discipline themselves , make the tough choices , and battle it out foe their dreams 

that person that changes everything for your family … that WILL be you !! 

STEP UP

DIG IN 

GO DELIVER FOR THE PEOPLE YOU LOVE

DROP A 🔥🔥 IF THIS SPOKE TO
YOU

node.text:
so many times you are going to feel like you are not enough 

like you have nothing to say 

like why would anyone want to follow you :

it’s in those times that you need to speak the loudest

it’s in those feelings of inadequacy you need to lead the boldest 

it’s in those moments of doubt that you are EVERYTHING someone needs

here’s the key: the enemy doesn’t need to destroy you if he can discourage you 

he uses discouragement and doubt to keep you from your destiny 

so speak up and lead loud … you are enough 

Drop a 🙌🏻 if this spoke to you

node.text:
sometimes life is going to ask you to risk it all for a dream no one can see but you…. 

and in that moment life will demand a choice ….

to pursue a life of increidble adventure and impact, a wake you up in the morning and keep you up at night around the world completely amazing sort of life….

or to play it safe and never really live at all, to let all the things you think you’re not stop you from being all that you are 

the purpose of life isn’t to arrive safely at death  but rather to live wide open, to dream a big dream, to make life a daring adventure… 

what have you chosen? 

it’s not too late to choose differently 

to take the path less traveled 

Dream Big, Dreamer 

Drop a 🔥 if you choose your dreams over your doubts 

#dreamer #motivationalposts #leadershipgoals

node.text:
Do you believe in miracles? 

This is Zac And He is my miracle (one of many) 

i want to share this with you to inspire you, to help you build your faith, and to encourage you to believe one more time 

many of you are believing for miracles in your life, you have situations that in the natural seem impossible. 

it may be a health challenge for a loved one, or a financial breakthrough for your family or maybe restoration of a broken relationship

you have been praying and believing but it just doesn’t seem like anything’s happening 

here’s my message for you : KEEP YOUR HOPES UP, BELIEVE AGAIN, ASK AGAIN

2.5 years ago Zac was diagnosed with UC which is a digestive auto immune disorder 
there is no cure only treatment 

the problem was treatment after treatment was unsuccessful. He got to the point about a year ago that He was down to 62 pounds
He didn’t have the strength to even stand up and walk around. He was on mega doses of steroids , biologics , and an incredibly restrictive diet.. and still nothing 

we prayed and believed and researched and it seemed no matter what we did he didn’t respond.

We got to the point where the doctor told us that if he didn’t have a turn around in 48 hours they would have to take his colon 

it was devastating, we were tired of believing and tired of fighting… 

that was almost exactly one year ago.

God stepped in and turned that situation and did what we couldn’t and what medicine couldn’t 

We just got his latest labs back and his numbers are nothing short of an INCREDIBLE MIRACLE 

He’s off all medication except for 1 and is starting baseball this week 

friends it’s never too late for God to change the situation Believe again pray again stir your faith up again 

YOUR MIRACLE IS ON THE WAY 

drop a 🙌🏻 if this spoke to you

node.text:
God didn’t make losers…. we learn that all by ourselves! 

but here’s the truth: I don’t believe there is such a thing as a “loser” …only people who haven’t developed WINNING HABITS 

see we don’t choose our lives; at least not directly…. we choose our habits and our habits choose our lives 

Here’s the great news

1. you created the habits you have 
2. you can choose to create new ones
3. your can decide to become consistent with the habits that move the needle in your life… it’s YOUR CHOICE! 

ultimately it’s the little things done daily that create the Big results that everyone’s looking for …

and YOU can do those little things!

Drop a 💯 if you are committed to creating better habits in your life! 

#mindsetmastery #successhabits #businesstip

node.text:
To everyone who told me No…. thank you !

To everyone who talked about me behind my back and said i would never make it… thank you !

To those who tried to push me down other paths, who wanted me to live THEIR dream instead of my own … thank you !

To everyone who doubted me and tried to get me to doubt myself … thank you! 

To everyone who started with me but didn’t finish … thank you! 

without YOU i wouldn’t have had the FIRE INSIDE to do something BIG the TENACITY to keep going and the UNDERSTANDING to see that beaten paths are for beaten people

Head up, shoulders back , the things that were supposed to hurt  you have instead made  you stronger 🔥🔥

you are unbreakable 

and that will ultimately make you unbeatable 

Drop a 🔥🔥 if this spoke to you

node.text:
Long post alert!! 

In life, leadership, and business, our trials don’t ever go away or get smaller;  we just get better

as we develop our level of mental toughness the things that used to phase us and stop us dead in our tracks no longer hinder us

it’s not that they’re not there, it’s just that we’ve risen above them

Think about it kind of like weightlifting. in the beginning it could be very challenging to lift a 50 pound dumbbell

but after years of consistent strength training, lifting that exact same dumbbell is  not a challenge anymore….

what happened? 

did the dumbell get smaller? 

no, we got stronger …

that’s why being purposeful about developing your mind and your level of mental toughness is essential to winning

you simply won’t go to the next level until you are strong enough to handle its challenges

here’s 3 ideas to help you develop your mental toughness:

1. seek out challenges - most people spend their life running away from things that challenge them or make them uncomfortable mentally tough people seek out the challenges because they know it makes them stronger

2. understand you are the problem and the solution - mentally weak people spend a lot of their time blaming others and circumstances, mentally strong people focus on developing themselves

3. don’t worry about things you can’t control - Mentally strong people worry about Controlling themselves, their attitude, and their work ethic. mentally weak people spend inordinate amounts of time trying to control things they have no control over like other people

toughen up baby everything you want is in the other side of getting stronger 

drop a 🔥🔥 if this spoke to you 

#lead #wisdom #mindset #mentaltoughness

node.text:
so many people will live their entire lives and NEVER live their dreams 

Remember this: the longer it takes you to reach your dream the less time you have to live it.

here’s three of my favorite tips to live your dreams FAST 

1. Get Clear - it’s not that what we want is too hard it’s that there are clearer paths to lesser goals. when you don’t know what you want any path will get you there
 
2. Decide upfront how you will handle setbacks - failure is par for the course on the path to success. Its unavoidable. But its how you choose to respond to it that determines your destiny. Well managed failure is one of the greatest causes of success 

3. You can’t be for sale - your dream isn’t negotiable.. there is no price on your destiny. You have to have the mindset that “I will until” , a whatever it takes as long as it takes mentality .. quitting isn’t in your vocabulary.

2 Keys to Dealing with Imposter Syndrome -

first of all, let’s define it 

imposter syndrome is where you feel like you aren’t good enough, prepared enough ,knowledgeable enough, or worthy of your current position in life …

like if people knew the real you maybe you wouldn’t be where you are …

Here’s the Truth: I’ve dealt with this most of my professional career … 

but here’s the key- imposter syndrome is both REAL and GOOD if you use it wisely 

Here’s 2 Keys to winning inspite of  imposter syndrome :

1. Remember You bring value: No matter where you are you have value to bring to people. You might not be at the goal but you are further along your path than those coming behind you and they will find great value in the lessons you’ve learned ahead of them.

2. Imposter Syndrome Is your subconscious telling you to improve. You feel uncomfortable because you KNOW you could be better than you are. Use that feeling to push you towards developing your skills and abilities at a greater level 

never ever forget this truth : DONT LET WHAT YOU THINK YOU AREN’T STOP YOU FROM EVERYTHING YOU ARE

node.text:
I’ve never been the best at anything

it almost everything that I’ve ever done there have been people who have been far more talented than I 

but life and success are a marathon not a sprint and hard work beats talent when talent isn’t working hard

no matter where you’re starting from or how far behind you think you might be, remember that somebody else’s game has virtually no effect on how you play your game. 

 I would like to share with you three things that helped me play my game

1. Learning myself- I think the first step to really succeeding is being very clear on who you are, what you want and why you want it.  you also need to know HOW you are : in other words, what are the things that tend to distract or immobilize you and how do you eliminate those from your life? how are you motivated and how do you leverage those things to keep going long after other people stop

2. self improving daily- we can’t go into a bright new future our same old junky self. The fact is we’ve gotten as far as we’re ever going to get with the mindset and skill set we currently have. if we want to upgrade our results we’ve got a upgrade our  thinking belief systems and actions.

3. be relentless- how bad do you want it? No, really, how bad do you want it? What’s it gonna take to get you to quit? what’s it going to take to get you to break?  if you wanna win big in life you’re gonna have to go way past those things. most of success is about holding on after everybody else let’s go. it’s about believing one more time, dreaming one more time, going for it one more time; and then doing it again tomorrow and the day after that and the day after that for years. 

so what’s the point of this? 

You don’t have to be the best to win in a big way or to live an incredible life and make a big difference. 

you do however  have to start, you have to show up ,you have to get better consistently and you have to be committed to your dream and your goal no matter what life throws at you. 

 the best part is none of those things take any talent you can choose those choices right here right now
